    <h1 class="wikiTitle">AmphetaOutlinesWishList</h1>
<div id="wikiContent">
<a name="PageTop"></a>
    <div class="wikiMeta">Revision r1.12 - 02 Jun 2003 - 16:28 GMT - <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/TWikiGuest">TWikiGuest</a> <!--META{"parent" prefix=">br /<Parents: "}%--></div>
<p />
<ul>
<li> Name
<ul>
<li> Starting to go beyond just outlines.
</li>
<li> Just <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/AmphetaDesk">AmphetaDesk</a>, leave template-land and start hacking core code?
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> UI
<ul>
<li> Even more lightweight HTML
</li>
<li> Hidden iframe / frame in which to perform web actions without a full page refresh?
<ul>
<li> Just use a pop-up?  Or replace pop-ups?
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Pagination of channels, to cut down on HTML loaded all at once
<ul>
<li> Slows down visual scan in one page via page-down
</li>
<li> May speed up overall scan by making each page quicker to load?
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Do something DHTMLish to dynamically load item content into page?
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Blog posting page
<ul>
<li> Based on <a href="http://search.cpan.org/search?mode=all&amp;query=Net::Blogger" title="CPAN search for Net::Blogger">CPAN:Net::Blogger</a>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Subscription categorization / grouping
<ul>
<li> Store category / groups in channel metadata
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Shopping cart
<ul>
<li> Queue up URLs to visit after one has finished skimming the aggregator page
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Personal History
<ul>
<li> Record &amp; track items visited / clicked in aggregator
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Archival
<ul>
<li> Store up and index all items ever seen in <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/RSS">RSS</a> feeds, even once unsubscribed.
</li>
<li> Requires a flexible, generalized persistence layer (vs simple XML files)
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Temporary / expiring subscriptions 
<ul>
<li> ie. For comment feeds
</li>
<li> Set to unsubscribe given X days of inactivity.
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Permanent, lightweight, rarely checked subscriptions
<ul>
<li> What if someone discovers a post 1 year later and comments?  I'd <strong>like</strong> to be notified.
<ul>
<li> Delete stored data for channel, very rarely check channel?
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Event feed from intrusion detection system?
</li>
<li> Annual event of short duration with a news site? (ie. Burning Man, Renaissance Festivals)
</li>
<li> Barely ever should change, but high priority when it does
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Vary channel polling frequency
<ul>
<li> Observe when channel changes, come up with a fitting polling frequency
</li>
<li> Double time between polls if a given poll comes up unchanged?
<ul>
<li> Doubling too much - ie. Yearly updated feed gets updated after 1 year, 1 day
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Polling frequency will tend to decrease with unchanging channels (ie. old comment feeds)
</li>
<li> Honor <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/RSS">RSS</a> extension module tags that specify update times
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Enhanced bookmarklet for autodetected subscription
<ul>
<li> Specify expiry period &amp; category
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Multiple sources of positive &amp; negative channel/item feedback
<ul>
<li> Clicks on item titles
</li>
<li> Detect &amp; count clicks on links encoded in item description
</li>
<li> Tree expansion, item manually made visible
</li>
<li> Manual karma / rating
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Machine learning &amp; assistance
<ul>
<li> Bayesian filtering of interesing items to highlight?
</li>
<li> Crawl blog neighborhood to find likely new interesting subscriptions?
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Preferences
<ul>
<li> Channel set to be fully expanded or collapsed by default
</li>
<li> Give priority to channel regardless of metrics
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Simple GUI Features
<ul>
<li> Category Folders, for grouping of related feeds
</li>
<li> possibility of changing the settings for the aging of feeds
        (e.g. how many hours must have passed so that an item is "old")
</li>
<li> allow for manual changing of aging (checkbox to go ahead and get rid of item, perhaps?)
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
